Reasoning: The paper discusses the use of wireless sensor networks and cloud computing for health monitoring, which falls under the category of networked and distributed systems (cs.NI). The use of a neural network for determining the state of patients suggests a machine learning (cs.LG) component to the system. The focus on health monitoring and wearable sensors suggests a human-computer interaction (cs.HC) aspect to the research. The use of cloud computing and machine learning algorithms also suggests a focus on data analytics (cs.MA). Finally, the paper discusses the use of wireless communication technologies, which could fall under the category of data communications (cs.DC).
